covered: Valid Request: Default retrieval and parameterized requests (offset/limit, boolean flags, and audit) are covered with multiple scenarios.
Empty Response: Tests cover empty data sets (no accounts) and offset beyond data, ensuring an empty JSON array is returned.

Pagination & Query Parameters: Extensive coverage of valid and invalid query parameter combinations, including offset, limit, accountWithBalance, accountWithBalanceAndCBA, audit, and extra/unknown parameters being ignored.
Authorization: Tests verify 401 responses for missing or invalid credentials.

Error Handling: Tests cover invalid values (negative/zero offset, negative/zero limit, invalid audit value, malformed booleans and integers) and invalid HTTP method; large query strings produce 414/400 as appropriate.
Security: Tests cover SQL injection and XSS attempts in parameters.
Performance & Scale: Large data volume and performance scenarios (10k accounts, limit 1000, with performance threshold checks) and degraded system under load.
Reliability & Recovery: Tests for transient network errors and recovery after failure; retries yield correct results.
Integration: Dependency service unavailability and data consistency with audit logs.
Edge Cases & Boundary Conditions: Tests for maximum/minimum parameter values, partial inputs, extra parameters ignored, no parameters provided, offset=0, and limit cap scenarios.
Backward Compatibility & Regression: Tests cover boundary conditions and existing API contract compatibility (offset/limit behavior and regression scenarios).
Accessibility: Screen-reader compatibility checks and descriptive error messages.
gaps: Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) or 304 responses.
Rate Limiting: No tests for throttling or rate-limiting behavior under bursty load.
HEAD/OPTIONS methods: No explicit tests for HEAD/OPTIONS against this endpoint (only 405 for invalid POST).
recommendations: Add tests for caching semantics (ETag, Cache-Control) including 304 responses and cache invalidation checks.
Introduce rate-limiting/throttling tests under bursty/concurrent access.
Add tests for HEAD/OPTIONS support to ensure proper method handling.
Expand integration coverage with audit-log cross-checks across multiple services for end-to-end consistency.
Enhance performance testing with more realistic latency targets across varying data sizes and environments.
